articles.title: Asian Champions Trophy Hockey: India knock out Pakistan with 4-0 win, finish as table toppers in group stage - India Today
articles.description: India defeated Pakistan 4-0 in their Asian Champions Trophy clash on Wednesday (August 9) to finish as table toppers at the Mayor Radhakrishnan Hockey Stadium in Chennai.
articles.content: Skipper Harmanpreet Singh scored twice as India defeated arch-rivals Pakistan 4-0 in their final round-robin league match here on Wednesday to advance to the semifinals unbeaten. India now leads the … [+2395 chars]
